    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed the required gradation level. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, required Gradation 3, achieved Gradation 2) is acknowledged; the validation team determined that the single ASTM F1717 standard condition is sufficient for the current submission given the medium model risk level and the availability of corroborating bench data. All three quantities of interest satisfy the pre-specified acceptance bounds. The FEA modeling framework is accepted as adequately credible for the stated COU. Note: all validation results were generated under ModelConfiguration ansys-mechanical-2026-q1-build-7-rc2, which the engineering team assessed as effectively equivalent to the production release ansys-mechanical-2026-q1-build-7; the validation suite was not re-executed under the released version.",
